scoringPlays.text: Jared Scott 23 Yd pass from Josh Allen (Cooper Rothe Kick)
Austin Conway 11 Yd pass from Josh Allen (Cooper Rothe Kick)
Jonathan Ward 74 Yd pass from Shane Morris (Michael Armstrong Kick)
C.J. Johnson 45 Yd pass from Josh Allen (Cooper Rothe Kick)
Jonathan Ward 3 Yd Run (Michael Armstrong Kick)
Carl Granderson 58 Yd Fumble Return (Cooper Rothe Kick)

videos.description: Wyoming's Josh Allen drops back and zips a strike to Jared Scott for the 23-yard score to go up 7-0.
videos.headline: Allen shows off NFL arm with TD strike

videos.description: Wyoming's Taniela Lolohea sacks Shane Morris, knocking the ball loose and Wyoming recovers on Central Michigan's 24-yard line.
videos.headline: Wyoming keeps momentum with strip-sack

videos.description: Wyoming's Josh Allen finds Austin Conway for his second TD throw in the first quarter. Allen only had one total first-quarter touchdown pass in the regular season.
videos.headline: Wyoming capitalizes with Allen TD throw

videos.description: Shane Morris patiently finds Jonathan Ward on the play-action wheel route, and Ward stays in bounds as he dives for the pylon to complete the 74-yard score.
videos.headline: Central Michigan strikes back with play-action TD

videos.description: Austin Conway hauls in the 13-yard pass with one hand to convert the first down.
videos.headline: Conway's one-handed grab keeps Wyoming drive alive

videos.description: Josh Allen drops back and throws a 45-yard pass to C.J. Johnson who catches it in stride in the end zone to go up 21-7.
videos.headline: Allen launches 3rd TD pass of first quarter

videos.description: CMU QB Shane Morris overthrows his receiver in the middle of the field and the errant pass is intercepted by Andrew Wingard.
videos.headline: Wyoming picks off overthrow

videos.description: Central Michigan's Shane Morris' pass is deflected at the line and Logan Wilson comes down with the interception for Wyoming.
videos.headline: Wyoming defense forces another turnover

videos.description: Wyoming head coach Craig Bohl says that Josh Allen's play is resulting in points on the scoreboard, but there's a lot of football to be played in the second half.
videos.headline: Wyoming rides Josh Allen to first-half lead

videos.description: Wyoming's Tyler Hall cuts off the slant and makes the pick, but doesn't escape a suplex-tackle before the play ends.
videos.headline: Halls catches INT, gets suplexed

videos.description: Central Michigan's Jonathan Ward reaches for the goal line to score as Central Michigan cuts the deficit to 30-14 in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Ward keeps Central Michigan in it with TD reach

videos.description: Wyoming knocks the ball from Central Michigan's Shane Morris, Carl Granderson scoops the fumble and returns it to the house to go up 37-14 in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Cowboys defense stampedes to rumble-six

videos.description: Wyoming gets the ball back with a big lead and little time left after Marcus Epps intercepts Shane Morris' overthrow.
videos.headline: Wyoming forces 7th turnover with INT

videos.description: Wyoming quarterback Josh Allen throws for 3 touchdowns against Central Michigan and speaks about what it meant to him to play in the bowl game.
videos.headline: Allen on bowl game win: 'It's everything I've dreamed about'
